vcpkg-tool-ccache provides ccache, a compiler cache that speeds up recompilation.

## Usage

To enable ccache for vcpkg builds, set the environment variable:

```bash
export VCPKG_USE_CCACHE=1  # Linux/macOS
```

```powershell
$env:VCPKG_USE_CCACHE = "1"  # Windows
```

Then install any port:

```bash
vcpkg install <port>
```

## Configuration

CCCache can be configured via environment variables:

- `CCACHE_DIR` - Cache directory (default: `<vcpkg-root>/.ccache`)
- `CCACHE_MAXSIZE` - Maximum cache size (default: 10G)
- `CCACHE_BASEDIR` - Base directory for relative paths (auto-set by vcpkg)

## Statistics

View cache statistics:

```bash
<vcpkg-root>/installed/<triplet>/tools/ccache/ccache -s
```

Or add ccache to your PATH:

```bash
ccache -s
```

## Benefits

- Speeds up rebuilds of the same port
- Speeds up builds across similar triplets (x64-windows, x64-windows-release)
- Speeds up feature testing (testing different feature combinations)
- Especially beneficial in CI/CD pipelines

## CMake Integration

The port automatically provides `CMAKE_C_COMPILER_LAUNCHER` and `CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER_LAUNCHER` when enabled.

For manual integration in your CMakeLists.txt:

```cmake
find_package(vcpkg-tool-ccache CONFIG REQUIRED)
vcpkg_enable_ccache()
```
